*log1p*

(PHP 4 >= 4.1.0, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

log1p â€” Returns log(1 + number), computed in a way that is accurate even when
the value of number is close to zero

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  log1p(float $num): float~

log1p() returns log(1 + {num}) computed in a way that is accurate even when the
value of {num} is close to zero. |log| might only return log(1) in this case
due to lack of precision.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  The argument to process

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

log(1 + {num})

===============================================================================
[ See Also ]

 * |expm1| - Returns exp($num) - 1, computed in a way that is accurate even
  when the value of number is close to zero
 * |log| - Natural logarithm
 * |log10| - Base-10 logarithm


